Dexter uses the autotools (./configure && make && sudo make install ) 
and depends on:
- pcre
- libxml2
- libxslt (with exslt)
- bison/yacc
- lex/flex
- argp (comes with GNU C Lib, non-Linux OS should have argp-standalone 
  packages)

Debian/Ubuntu:
------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo apt-get install libxslt1-dev libpcre3-dev build-essential bison flex
./configure
make
sudo make install

Mac OS X with MacPorts:
------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo port install pcre bison flex libxslt argp-standalone
./configure
make
sudo make install

Windows:
------------------------------------------------------------------------
I've made no attempt to be Windows-friendly, yet.  I'd love some 
contributions!

Other OS/Configurations:
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Haven't tried.